				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/agree with above post
<br />

<br />
but I would prefer if it weren't just an aa ability; all pet classes should be able to zone with their pets from the time they get them. I'm sure it's technically feasible; code the pet as an "item" for zoning purposes, or maybe a new nondispellable "petbuff" slot (similar to the original BL pet buff icon, but with more detail).
<br />

<br />
In every sense, pets are *part* of their parent character; no beastlord, mage, or necromancer would play without one under normal circumstances. They are included in class balancing. Every other class zones with their character intact; we three (plus chanters, shamans, sks, druids, and others with minor pets) do not.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
